The paper discusses the use of deep generative models for abnormality detection in medical imaging, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of auto-encoder-based models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging data, which is a sub-field of multimedia (cs.MM).
